# .shopifyignore — files excluded from `shopify theme push` and `shopify theme dev`
#
# Strategy:
#   - Code files (sections/, snippets/, assets/, layout/, locales/, config/settings_schema.json)
#     are always pushed.
#   - Data files (config/settings_data.json, templates/*.json) WERE previously
#     ignored to protect merchant edits. Now allowed because:
#       1. `shopify theme dev` needs templates/*.json to render the storefront
#          preview locally — without them every page returns 404.
#       2. The submission workflow uses `shopify theme package` from a clean
#          baseline tag (e.g. submission-baseline-r185), not from the live
#          working tree, so placeholder content is preserved at packaging time.
#       3. Production merchant content lives in a separate non-GitHub-connected
#          store, never pushed from this codebase.
#
# Theme Store-banned patterns below (.md files, docs/) MUST stay ignored —
# Shopify rejects uploads containing them.

# Theme Store ban-list — never push any of these
*.md
docs/*
references/*
.github/*
.theme-check.yml
.editorconfig
.gitignore
.prettierrc*

# Dev-time theme-check config that Shopify's backend doesn't need
.shopifyrc.json

# Node / local dev artefacts
node_modules/*
*.log
.env
.env.*

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor backups
*.swp
*~
*.bak

# Local theme-package zip artefacts (output of `shopify theme package`).
# Pushing one in would create a nested-zip recursion in the live theme.
*.zip

# Local Claude Code agent state — never ship to storefront
.claude/*
.claude-code/*
